					<div id=3D"contentSub"><div id=3D"mw-content-subtitle"></div></div>
				=09
				=09
					<div id=3D"mw-content-text" class=3D"mw-body-content"><div class=3D"mw=
-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang=3D"en" dir=3D"ltr"><div role=3D"note" c=
lass=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">"QRD" redirects here. For the Ma=
ltese locality, see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qrendi" title=
=3D"Qrendi">Qrendi</a>.</div><div class=3D"shortdescription nomobile noexce=
rpt noprint searchaux" style=3D"display:none">Matrix decomposition</div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_algebra" title=3D"Lin=
ear algebra">linear algebra</a>, a <b>QR decomposition</b>, also known as a=
 <b>QR factorization</b> or <b>QU factorization</b>, is a <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_decomposition" title=3D"Matrix decomposition=
">decomposition</a> of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_(m=
athematics)" title=3D"Matrix (mathematics)">matrix</a> <i>A</i> into a prod=
uct <i>A</i>&nbsp;=3D&nbsp;<i>QR</i> of an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Orthonormal_matrix" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Orthonormal mat=
rix">orthonormal matrix</a> <i>Q</i> and an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Upper_triangular_matrix" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Upper tri=
angular matrix">upper triangular matrix</a> <i>R</i>. QR decomposition is o=
ften used to solve the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_leas=
t_squares_(mathematics)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linear least square=
s (mathematics)">linear least squares</a> (LLS) problem and is the basis fo=
r a particular <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eigenvalue_algorith=
m" title=3D"Eigenvalue algorithm">eigenvalue algorithm</a>, the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_algorithm" title=3D"QR algorithm">QR algor=
ithm</a>.
</p>
<meta property=3D"mw:PageProp/toc">
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Cases_and_definitions">Case=
s and definitions</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-edit=
section-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?ti=
tle=3DQR_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit sec=
tion: Cases and definitions"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsec=
tion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Square_matrix">Square matri=
x</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DQR_decompo=
sition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: Square mat=
rix"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></=
span></div>
<p>Any real <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_matrix" title=
=3D"Square matrix">square matrix</a> <i>A</i> may be decomposed as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e A=3DQR,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A=3DQR,}</ann=
otation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/d4bc683fc8c2ab81b7bd7729d3634d0ae007d704" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:9.091ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
=3DQR,}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>where <i>Q</i> is an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthogonal=
_matrix" title=3D"Orthogonal matrix">orthogonal matrix</a> (its columns are=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthogonal" class=3D"mw-redirect"=
 title=3D"Orthogonal">orthogonal</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Unit_vector" title=3D"Unit vector">unit vectors</a> meaning <span class=
=3D"nowrap"><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span =
class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: non=
e;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\display=
style Q^{\textsf {T}}=3DQ^{-1}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>Q</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext mathvariant=3D"sans-serif">T</mtext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>Q</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Q^{\textsf {T=
}}=3DQ^{-1}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/af56244b2369b6bc6bfa6b5487786952843b5d2c" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:10.459ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle Q^=
{\textsf {T}}=3DQ^{-1}}"></span>)</span> and <i>R</i> is an upper <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triangular_matrix" title=3D"Triangular ma=
trix">triangular matrix</a> (also called right triangular matrix). If <i>A<=
/i> is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invertible_matrix" title=3D=
"Invertible matrix">invertible</a>, then the factorization is unique if we =
require the diagonal elements of <i>R</i> to be positive.
</p><p>If instead <i>A</i> is a complex square matrix, then there is a deco=
mposition <i>A</i> =3D <i>QR</i> where <i>Q</i> is a <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Unitary_matrix" title=3D"Unitary matrix">unitary matrix<=
/a> (so the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjugate_transpose" t=
itle=3D"Conjugate transpose">conjugate transpose</a> <span class=3D"nowrap"=
><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mw=
e-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math x=
mlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle Q^{\d=
agger }=3DQ^{-1}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mi>Q</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=80=A0<!-- =E2=80=A0 --></mo>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msup>
          <mi>Q</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle Q^{\dagger }=
=3DQ^{-1}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2edb0b2dfd97ec11ff1b691268ad42dee62c494b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:10.07ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle Q^{=
\dagger }=3DQ^{-1}}"></span>).</span>
</p><p>If <i>A</i> has <i>n</i> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Li=
nearly_independent" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linearly independent">li=
nearly independent</a> columns, then the first <i>n</i> columns of <i>Q</i>=
 form an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthonormal_basis" title=
=3D"Orthonormal basis">orthonormal basis</a> for the <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Column_space" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Column spac=
e">column space</a> of <i>A</i>. More generally, the first <i>k</i> columns=
 of <i>Q</i> form an orthonormal basis for the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Linear_span" title=3D"Linear span">span</a> of the first <i>k<=
/i> columns of <i>A</i> for any <span class=3D"nowrap">1 =E2=89=A4 <i>k</i>=
 =E2=89=A4 <i>n</i></span>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Trefethen_1-0" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_decomposition#cite_note-=
Trefethen-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup>  The fact that any column <i>k</i> of <i>A</i> only=
 depends on the first <i>k</i> columns of <i>Q</i> corresponds to the trian=
gular form of&nbsp;<i>R</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Trefethen_1-1" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_decomposition#cite_note=
-Trefethen-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Rectangular_matrix">Rectang=
ular matrix</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
QR_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: =
Rectangular matrix"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">]</span></span></div>
<p>More generally, we can factor a complex <i>m</i>=C3=97<i>n</i> matrix <i=
>A</i>, with <span class=3D"nowrap"><i>m</i> =E2=89=A5 <i>n</i></span>, as =
the product of an <i>m</i>=C3=97<i>m</i> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Unitary_matrix" title=3D"Unitary matrix">unitary matrix</a> <i>Q</i>=
 and an <i>m</i>=C3=97<i>n</i> upper triangular matrix <i>R</i>.  As the bo=
ttom (<i>m</i>=E2=88=92<i>n</i>) rows of an <i>m</i>=C3=97<i>n</i> upper tr=
iangular matrix consist entirely of zeroes, it is often useful to partition=
