" title=3D"Triangular matrix">triangular</a> form. First, we multiply <i>A<=
/i> with the Householder matrix <i>Q</i><sub>1</sub> we obtain when we choo=
se the first matrix column for <b>x</b>. This results in a matrix <i>Q</i><=
sub>1</sub><i>A</i> with zeros in the left column (except for the first row=
).
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
