<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Advantages_and_disadvantage=
s_3">Advantages and disadvantages</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/w/index.php?title=3DQR_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" =
title=3D"Edit section: Advantages and disadvantages"><span>edit</span></a><=
span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The QR decomposition via Givens rotations is the most involved to implem=
ent, as the ordering of the rows required to fully exploit the algorithm is=
 not trivial to determine. However, it has a significant advantage in that =
each new zero element <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inli=
ne"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"di=
splay: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D=
"{\displaystyle a_{ij}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mi>j</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a_{ij}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/ebea6cd2813c330c798921a2894b358f7b643917" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.005ex; width:2.707ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a_{=
ij}}"></span> affects only the row with the element to be zeroed (<i>i</i>)=
 and a row above (<i>j</i>). This makes the Givens rotation algorithm more =
bandwidth efficient and parallelizable than the Householder reflection tech=
nique.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Connection_to_a_determinant=
_or_a_product_of_eigenvalues">Connection to a determinant or a product of e=
