</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Column_pivoting">Column piv=
oting</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DQR_dec=
omposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Colum=
n pivoting"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</=
span></span></div>
<p>Pivoted QR differs from ordinary Gram-Schmidt in that it takes the large=
st remaining column at the beginning of each new step=E2=80=94column pivoti=
ng=E2=80=94<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/QR_decomposition#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and thus intro=
duces a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permutation_matrix" title=
=3D"Permutation matrix">permutation matrix</a> <i>P</i>:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e AP=3DQR\quad \iff \quad A=3DQRP^{\textsf {T}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>P</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
        <mspace width=3D"thickmathspace"></mspace>
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=9F=BA<!-- =E2=9F=BA --></mo>
        <mspace width=3D"thickmathspace"></mspace>
        <mspace width=3D"1em"></mspace>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>Q</mi>
        <mi>R</mi>
        <msup>
          <mi>P</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext mathvariant=3D"sans-serif">T</mtext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle AP=3DQR\quad =
\iff \quad A=3DQRP^{\textsf {T}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/816b6758d11f883df12fc089e0366ce538a46ec5" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:33.349ex; height:3.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle AP=
=3DQR\quad \iff \quad A=3DQRP^{\textsf {T}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>Column pivoting is useful when <i>A</i> is (nearly) <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rank_deficient" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Rank de=
ficient">rank deficient</a>, or is suspected of being so. It can also impro=
ve numerical accuracy. <i>P</i> is usually chosen so that the diagonal elem=
ents of <i>R</i> are non-increasing: <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-ma=
th-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a1=
1y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Mat=
hML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \left|r_{11}\right|\geq \left|r_{22}\right|\=
geq \cdots \geq \left|r_{nn}\right|}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow>
          <mo>|</mo>
          <msub>
            <mi>r</mi>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mn>11</mn>
            </mrow>
